<div class="page"><header class="brand"><div class="logo">FIXFY</div><div class="meta">Getfixfy Ltd &middot; Co. No. 15406523</div></header>
  <h1 class="title">PLATFORM<span class="accent">TERMS OF USE</span></h1>
  <p class="lead">These Platform Terms of Use (the &ldquo;Terms&rdquo;) govern access to and use of the Fixfy platform operated by <span class="party">GETFIXFY LTD</span>, a company incorporated in England and Wales under company number 15406523, with its registered office at 124 City Road, London EC1V 2NX, United Kingdom (&ldquo;Fixfy&rdquo;, the &ldquo;Company&rdquo;, &ldquo;we&rdquo; or &ldquo;us&rdquo;).</p>
  <p class="lead">By registering for, accessing or using the platform as a trade, contractor or service provider (the &ldquo;Partner&rdquo;, &ldquo;you&rdquo; or &ldquo;your&rdquo;), you agree to be bound by these Terms.</p>

  <div class="callout"><strong>Agency model.</strong> Fixfy operates as a disclosed agent that introduces maintenance and facilities jobs from business clients to vetted Partners. Fixfy is not the end client and does not itself perform the works. Fixfy facilitates introductions, coordination, invoicing and payment through the platform.</div>

  <h2 class="section">1.&nbsp;&nbsp;Definitions</h2>
  <ul class="dash">
    <li><strong>Platform</strong> &mdash; the Fixfy web and mobile applications, portal and related systems.</li>
    <li><strong>Client</strong> &mdash; a business that requests maintenance, repair or facilities services through the Platform.</li>
    <li><strong>Job</strong> &mdash; a specific unit of work requested by a Client and allocated to a Partner.</li>
    <li><strong>Partner Content</strong> &mdash; data, documents, certifications and information submitted by the Partner.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="section">2.&nbsp;&nbsp;Eligibility and Vetting</h2>
  <p><span class="sub">2.1</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;The Partner warrants that it operates as an independent business and holds all licences, qualifications, insurance and certifications required to perform the Services lawfully in the United Kingdom, including where applicable Gas Safe, NICEIC, NAPIT, EICR and Fire Safety certifications.</p>
  <p><span class="sub">2.2</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;The Partner shall keep all certifications, insurance and qualification records current and shall upload valid evidence to the Platform on request. Fixfy may suspend a Partner whose records are expired, missing or unverifiable.</p>
  <p><span class="sub">2.3</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;Fixfy reserves the right to vet, approve, decline or remove any Partner at its discretion.</p>

  <h2 class="section">3.&nbsp;&nbsp;Use of the Platform</h2>
  <p><span class="sub">3.1</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;The Partner shall use the Platform only for legitimate business purposes connected to the provision of Services to Clients introduced by Fixfy.</p>
  <p><span class="sub">3.2</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;The Partner shall not misuse, disrupt, reverse-engineer, copy or attempt to gain unauthorised access to the Platform or its data.</p>
  <p><span class="sub">3.3</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;Access credentials are personal to the Partner and must be kept secure. The Partner is responsible for all activity under its account.</p>

  <h2 class="section">4.&nbsp;&nbsp;Jobs, Pricing and Payment</h2>
  <p><span class="sub">4.1</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;Jobs are presented to the Partner with either pre-set pricing or a request for a quote. The Partner is free to accept or decline any Job.</p>
  <p><span class="sub">4.2</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;All payment for Jobs must be processed through the Platform&rsquo;s integrated payment system. Fixfy applies its commission to each Job in accordance with the rates notified to the Partner.</p>
  <p><span class="sub">4.3</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;Invoicing for completed Jobs is handled by self-billing, governed by the separate Self-Billing Agreement which the Partner must accept.</p>
  <p><span class="sub">4.4</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;Any guarantee or service warranty offered by Fixfy applies only to Jobs booked, managed and paid through the Platform.</p>

  <h2 class="section">5.&nbsp;&nbsp;Anti-Circumvention</h2>
  <p><span class="sub">5.1</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;The Partner shall not solicit, divert or transact with a Client introduced through the Platform outside the Platform, whether directly or indirectly, for any Job that originated through Fixfy.</p>
  <p><span class="sub">5.2</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;The Partner shall not share, expose or use Client contact details to bypass the Platform. Breach of this clause may result in immediate suspension, removal and recovery of lost commission.</p>

  <h2 class="section">6.&nbsp;&nbsp;Standards and Conduct</h2>
  <p><span class="sub">6.1</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;The Partner shall perform all Services with reasonable skill and care, in compliance with applicable law, health and safety requirements and industry standards.</p>
  <p><span class="sub">6.2</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;The Partner shall meet agreed response windows, attendance windows and quality standards. Repeated failure may result in reduced Job allocation or removal.</p>

  <h2 class="section">7.&nbsp;&nbsp;Data and Records</h2>
  <p><span class="sub">7.1</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;Job history, Client records, documentation and operational data generated on the Platform remain the property of Fixfy and the relevant Client, and are made available to the Partner only for the purpose of delivering Services.</p>
  <p><span class="sub">7.2</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;Each party shall comply with applicable data protection law (including the UK GDPR and the Data Protection Act 2018) in respect of personal data processed through the Platform.</p>

  <h2 class="section">8.&nbsp;&nbsp;Independent Relationship</h2>
  <p><span class="sub">8.1</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;The Partner is an independent business. Nothing in these Terms creates any employment, worker, partnership, agency (beyond the disclosed introduction model) or joint-venture relationship between Fixfy and the Partner.</p>
  <p><span class="sub">8.2</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;The Partner is solely responsible for its own taxes, social security, insurance and obligations to its own personnel.</p>

  <h2 class="section">9.&nbsp;&nbsp;Liability</h2>
  <p><span class="sub">9.1</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;The Partner is solely responsible for the Services it performs and indemnifies Fixfy against claims arising from the Partner&rsquo;s acts, omissions, defective work or breach of these Terms.</p>
  <p><span class="sub">9.2</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;Nothing in these Terms limits liability for death or personal injury caused by negligence, fraud, or any liability that cannot be excluded by law.</p>

  <h2 class="section">10.&nbsp;&nbsp;Suspension and Termination</h2>
  <p><span class="sub">10.1</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;Fixfy may suspend or terminate a Partner&rsquo;s access at any time for breach of these Terms, expired certifications, or conduct that poses risk to Clients or the Platform.</p>
  <p><span class="sub">10.2</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;The Partner may stop using the Platform at any time. Obligations relating to confidentiality, anti-circumvention, data and accrued payment survive termination.</p>

  <h2 class="section">11.&nbsp;&nbsp;Changes to the Terms</h2>
  <p><span class="sub">11.1</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;Fixfy may update these Terms from time to time. Material changes will be notified through the Platform. Continued use after notification constitutes acceptance.</p>

  <h2 class="section">12.&nbsp;&nbsp;Governing Law</h2>
  <p><span class="sub">12.1</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;These Terms are governed by the laws of England and Wales. Disputes shall be subject to confidential arbitration in London under the LCIA Rules, with London as the seat and English as the language.</p>

  <div class="execution">
    <h2 class="exec">ACCEPTANCE</h2>
    <p>By clicking &ldquo;Sign&rdquo; / &ldquo;Accept&rdquo; in the Fixfy onboarding portal, or by signing below, the Partner confirms it has read, understood and agreed to these Platform Terms of Use.</p>
    <div class="sigwrap">
      <div class="sigcell">
        <div class="h">GETFIXFY LTD</div>
        <div class="org">Getfixfy Ltd</div>
        <div class="org">124 City Road, London EC1V 2NX</div>
        <div class="org">Co. No. 15406523</div>
        <div class="sigline"></div><div class="sigcap">Authorised signatory</div>
        <div class="sigline"></div><div class="sigcap">Date</div>
      </div>
      <div class="sigcell">
        <div class="h">THE PARTNER</div>
        <div class="org">&nbsp;</div>
        <div class="sigline"></div><div class="sigcap">Name / Business name</div>
        <div class="sigline"></div><div class="sigcap">Signature</div>
        <div class="sigline"></div><div class="sigcap">Date</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <footer class="foot"><span>Platform Terms of Use &middot; v2026 &mdash; Confidential</span><span>Getfixfy Ltd</span></footer></div>',
  true
);

